<HEADLINE> Israeli Arabs Riot at Independence Day Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Seven Israeli policemen and at
least two Israeli Arabs were injured on Sunday in clashes during an
independence day celebrations, police said.
</P>
<P>
The northern Israeli-Arab village Shfar Am was holding an
independence day celebration with the participation of Interior
Minister Natan Sharansky when about 300 demonstrators protesting
against the event clashed with the police, the police said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators threw stones at police and set fire to cars
and tires. The police fired tear gas and rubber-coated bullets at
the demonstrators after police were injured, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Israel celebrates officially its independence day on Wednesday.
Israeli Arabs have threatened to boycott the event for the first
time in Israel's 52-year history, Israel's Channel One television
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
