<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel to Close Palestinian Areas for Holidays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Israel will seal the Palestinian
areas during national holidays of Memorial Day and Independence
Day, preventing Palestinians in the West Bank and Gaza Strip from
entering Israel.
</P>
<P>
The closure, which is to last from Monday morning to Thursday
evening, will prevent thousands of Palestinians from reaching their
jobs in Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Memorial Day, honoring Israelis who have fallen in battle
and in terrorist attacks, begins Monday night and ends Tuesday
night with celebrations marking the 52nd anniversary of the
founding of Israel. Independence Day ends Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Israel often seals the Palestinian areas during national
holidays as a security measure. But the Palestinians complain that
the measure amounts to collective punishment for them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
