<HEADLINE> Arafat-Barak Summit Starts in Ramallah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The summit between Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat started
in the West Bank City of Ramallah Sunday evening to clear the
obstacles in the bilateral peace talks, Radio Israel reported.
</P>
<P>
The summit was also attended by Secretary of the Palestine
Liberation Organization Mahmoud Abbas, Speaker of Palestinian
Legislative Council Ahmed Qureia, Barak's political and security
adviser Danny Yatom and his Foreign Minister David Levy.
</P>
<P>
The summit focuses on the transfer of three villages near
Jerusalem to full Palestinian control, the difficulities facing
the final-status talks, and the dispute over the expansion of Maali
Adomim settlement, Palestinian sources said earlier on Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
