<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Denies Involvement in Lockerbie Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday rejected allegations by
foreign media that Iranians were involved in the Lockerbie bombing
in 1988.
</P>
<P>
These futile and baseless allegations are totally unacceptable,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi was quoted by the
Islamic News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman was amazed over the claims made in some interviews
and materials printed by some foreign media, saying the allegations
were made to influence the court hearing, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The bombing of Pan American Flight 103 over Lockerbie, Scotland
in December 1988 killed 259 people in the air and 11 people on the
ground.
</P>
<P>
The trial of two Libyan suspects is currently going on at a
special court in the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
