<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Djibouti Urges Arabs to Help Solve Somali Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Djiboutian President
Ismael Omar Guelleh on Sunday called on the Arab countries to help
solve the Somali crisis that tore the east African country apart.
</P>
<P>
Guelleh, who is on a visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE),
said that the Arabs must work for the restoration of peace and
strength of Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Djibouti proposed to raise a fund for solidarity with Somalia to
reconstruct the country in line with a scheme like the U.S. "
Marshal Project" for the reconstruction of western Europe after
World War II, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The Arabs should help the Somali people solve their problems,
the president added.
</P>
<P>
On his arrival here, the Djiboutian president said he will
discuss with UAE leaders the bilateral ties and regional and
international issues of common concern. It will provide an
opportunity to brief the UAE leaders on the Djiboutian initiative
of peace in Somalia, he said.
</P>
<P>
Guelleh and his party arrived here on Saturday on a visit to the
UAE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
