<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian FM Meets U.N. Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-
Shareh met here on Sunday U.N. Secretary General's special envoy
Tery Rod Larsen on the long-awaited Israeli withdrawal from south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed also the U.N. role in the implementation
of the Security Council resolutions No. 425 and 426, the Arab-
Syrian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Larsen and Shareh reviewed the results of Larsen's recent tour
of the region and the renewed Israeli offensive against Lebanese
civilian targets.
</P>
<P>
Shareh said Syria urged the U.N. to play its part in the
implementation of all Security Council resolutions, underscoring
the role of UNIFIL (United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon) in
this regard to abort any Israeli pretext to destabilize the
situation in the region.
</P>
<P>
Larsen arrived here earlier Sunday for a short visit to Syria as
part of his tour that took him to Lebanon and Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
