were battling U.N. peacekeepers in the interior of the West
African country while U.N. troops were reported mobilizing for
action in the nation's capital of Freetown. The rebels have taken
at least 300 U.N. peacekeepers hostage over the last week, with
another 200 missing.
</P>
<P>
The peacekeepers are mainly from Zambia, India,Kenya and
Nigeria and were dispatched to the West African country to monitor
a peace accord signed last July to end the nine-year civil war in
the country.  
