<HEADLINE> China to Produce More Quality Steel Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China's metallurgical industry will
focus its readjustment of product mix on developing and producing
more quality steel products, a senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Pu Haiqing, director of the State Administration of
Metallurgical Industry, said at the Congress "Steel 2000", that
most steel products China imports are of a high quality, such as
stainless and rolled sheet.
</P>
<P>
China is the world's largest steel producer with steel output
exceeding 100 million tons in the past four years. However, the
country still has to import some seven million tons of steel
products for special use.
</P>
<P>
The industrialization process in China, is placing huge demand
on the steel industry and higher quality and better services, Pu
said.
</P>
<P>
Sectors including automobiles, machinery products, household
appliances, petroleum and communications all needs high quality
steel products for upgrading, he added.
</P>
<P>
China is now aiming to sharpen the competitive edge of its
major steel producers by upgrading technology and merging its
enterprises. 
</P>
