<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Import More Manpower from Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Sunday expressed keen interest
to recruit more manpower from Bangladesh during high-level
official talks between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At the talks, visiting Kuwaiti State Minister for Foreign
Affairs Suleiman Majed Al-Shaheen and Bangladeshi State Minister
for Foreign Affairs Abul Hasan Chowdhury reviewed the bilateral
relationship between the two countries and decided to accelerate
cooperation in the economic and trade sectors.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury told reporters after the talks that at present, more
than 200,000 Bangladeshi citizens are working in Kuwait. On an
average,since 1996, Kuwait has been recruiting more than 20,000
skilled and semi-skilled workers from Bangladesh every year.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti state minister reaffirmed his country's interest in
recruiting more manpower from Bangladesh, and sought the
cooperation of Bangladesh, a member of the United Nations Security
Council, to coordinate in rescuing 600 Kuwaiti citizens from Iraqi
captivity and realizing compensation for war damage.
</P>
<P>
He said Bangladeshi citizens affected by the Iraqi invasion of
Kuwait in 1990 would also get their due compensation provided
Kuwait can realize it from Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
