<HEADLINE> People's Daily Calls for National Unity and Stability (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily, the leading
newspaper of the Communist Party of China (CPC), will publish a
commentary tomorrow, calling on the entire nation to ensure unity
and stability for the rejuvenation of China.
</P>
<P>
The article coincides with the first anniversary of the U.S.-
led NATO bombing of the Chinese embassy in Yugoslavia on May 8,
1999, resulting in heavy casualties and serious damage of the
embassy building.
</P>
<P>
"The same day one year ago, the U.S.-led NATO raided the
Chinese Embassy in Yugoslavia with missiles during its aggressive
war against Kosovo," it says, adding the bombing "shocked the
whole world."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government lodged a statement to severely condemn
the atrocity and demanded the U.S.-led NATO be held fully
accountable. Meanwhile, the Chinese people nationwide also staged
protest activities.
</P>
<P>
All peace-loving and just governments, organization and people
worldwide also condemned the brutal act and expressed their
support, it says.
</P>
<P>
In face of the arrogance and hegemonist behavior, the Chinese
people "were not frightened or crashed," the article says. On the
contrary, the brutal acts "triggered an outburst of patriotism,
determined the iron will of the Chinese people, and rejuvenated
their high zeal for construction."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000507.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
