<HEADLINE> People's Daily Calls for National Unity, Stability (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"As long as we maintain social stability under the firm
leadership of the Communist Party of China, China will be stronger
day by day, and no forces can do anything harmful to us," it says.
</P>
<P>
"There should be unity and stability in China," it adds.
</P>
<P>
Reform and opening-up is the way toward building a strong and
prosperous country, it notes, adding that in today's world, multi-
polarity is moving forward, and peace and development are the will
of the people.
</P>
<P>
"We should make full use of favorable opportunities, and
promote exchanges and cooperation with other countries, and firmly
pursue an independent foreign policy of peace, and develop
friendship and cooperation with other countries on the basis of
the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence," it says.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China firmly opposes hegemonism, and will never make
any concession on the matters relating to national sovereignty,
dignity and security while pursuing cooperation with other
countries, including western countries, in all areas based on the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence, it says.
</P>
<P>
Nothing can stop the Chinese people from rejuvenating their
nation no matter how difficult the road ahead is, the commentary
says, urging the entire Chinese people to work harder to build a
strong, prosperous, democratic and culturally advanced socialist
country under the leadership of the Communist Party of China
Central Committee with President Jiang Zemin at the core. 
</P>
