<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Invest Heavily in IT in Next Fiscal Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Federal Minister for
Science and Technology Atta-ur-Rehman said Sunday that an amount
of 15 billion rupees (300 million U.S. dollars) will be spent in
the next fiscal year in the field of science and information
technology (IT).
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a TV program, the minister said a country like
Pakistan needs to quickly absorb whatever technology exists around
and to utilize its human resources in a better way.
</P>
<P>
Atta-ur-Rehman said that a commitment has been made that
science and technology must serve as the engine for development
for the first time in the history of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
He said the Pakistani government will soon launch a crash
program to impart computer training to unemployed youth. This
program will be launched in all the big cities of the country, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
