<HEADLINE> Squillari Beats Haas to Retain Munich Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Franco Squillari of Argentina
returned his title at the Munich Open after crushing local
favorite Tommy Haas 6-4, 6-4 in the
final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The seventh seed spent only 71 minutes to down German Haas in a
one-sided final. Squillari's only previous tournament victory was
in Munich last year.
</P>
<P>
Haas, seeded third in the 525,000 U.S. dollars clay-court event,
has still to win a title on home ground. Sunday's final was his
third in a German tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
