<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Revolutionary Guards Start Military Maneuvers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The ground forces of Iran's elite
Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) on Sunday launched a two-
day military maneuvers in the central Kerman province.
</P>
<P>
A commander at the maneuver scene told the Islamic Republic News
Agency that the war game was aimed at boosting the forces'
defensive capabilities with employment of modern equipment.
</P>
<P>
He said that the maneuver would be carried out in three stages
in which the IRGC forces would launch offensive operations in 48
hours into the positions of the hypothetical enemies.
</P>
<P>
Some 2500 targets of the hypothetical enemies would be bombed in
the exercises, the commander said, adding that the IRGC ground
forces, armored division and air force would take part in the
military game.
</P>
<P>
The IRGC ground force commander Brigadier-General Mohammad Ali
Jaafari said Wednesday that the IRGC forces would launch three
separate maneuvers in Kerman province, Khorramshahr of southwestern
Khuzestan province and Najafabad, the central Isfahan province to
mark the recovery of Khorramshahr in the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
The exercises will include testing of the advanced military
hardware and boosting preparedness for rapid deployment operations
in the eastern and southern borders, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
