<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kasyanov Named Russian Acting Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin on
Sunday named First Deputy Prime Minster and Finance Minster
Mikhail Kasyanov as acting prime minister, the Interfax news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The appointment came shortly after Putin's inauguration
ceremony at the Kremlin earlier Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kasyanov, 42, has long been seen as the most probable candidate
for the premiership which Putin held before his inauguration.
</P>
<P>
Putin will soon submit Kasyanov's candidacy to the State Duma (
lower house of the parliament) and an easy approval is expected,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The current cabinet has tendered its resignation under the
Russian constitution.
</P>
<P>
Kasyanov, born on December 8, 1957, in the Solntsevo region of
Moscow, was educated at the Moscow Automobile and Road College in
1983, majoring in construction engineering.
</P>
<P>
After serving in the army, he used to work for a transportation
research center associated to the former Soviet Union's State
Committee for Construction.
</P>
<P>
In 1981-1990, Kasyanov worked at the Soviet State Planning
Committee, first as an engineer, later as a senior economist,
chief expert and section chief.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1993, Kasyanov served Russia's Ministry of
Economics on various posts and became head of the Finance
Ministry's foreign debt department in 1993.
</P>
<P>
He became deputy finance minister in 1995 and was named finance
minister in May 1999.
</P>
<P>
After former president Boris Yeltsin's surprise resignation on
December 31, 1999, Kasyanov was appointed first deputy prime
minister by then acting president Putin to look after the day-to-
day operation of the cabinet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
