<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ferry Sinks in Indonesia, Kills 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A least 21 persons died when a ferry
sank in the Tanjung Tial waters near Indonesia's Maluku provincial
capital Ambon on Sunday, Antara news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The ferry, heading from Gudang Arang port Waipirit port near
Ambon, sank at 10:00 a.m. local time when sailing on the Tanjung
Tial waters, some 40 kilometers east of Ambon, Antara said.
</P>
<P>
An official confirmed that 21 bodies had been found until 02:00
p.m. Security apparatus and local people living around the Tanjung
Tial coastal area are still looking for the other passengers of
the ill-fated ferry which might have carried hundreds of
passengers, overloading its capacity.
</P>
<P>
So far, the owner of the ferry or the related institutions
reached for confirmation have not given any detailed information
on the ferry.
</P>
<P>
According to Ano Tuatanasse, an eye witness, the ferry actually
left the Gudang Arang port on Saturday at 07:00 p.m., but waters
flooded into the ferry when it reached on the Air Salobar waters,
some two kilometers from Gudang Arang port.
</P>
<P>
"The captain then decided to go back to the port," said Ano who
managed to flee from the incident after swimming for hours with
his three friends.
</P>
<P>
The ferry was then sailed again on Sunday at 03:00 a.m. after
loading three cars, he added.
</P>
<P>
A truck driver taking part in the sail said when the ferry
reached Tial Bay waters, a wave three to five meters high hit the
ferry, damaging its left door.
</P>
<P>
"The second wave was the one that sank our ferry," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
