<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Wishes New President Putin Success  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Former President Boris Yeltsin on
Sunday wished the new Russian president, Vladimir Putin, success
in "performing the difficult presidential duties with dignity."
</P>
<P>
"We must build a new Russia. This job will be done by the
generation of young statesmen and politicians who firmly adhere to
the democratic values," Yeltsin said at an inauguration ceremony
for Putin in the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
"We have gone through many hardships and setbacks. But we can
be proud of what we have achieved -- Russia has changed because we
have been guarding Russia as the most valued treasure and we have
been consistently defending our main gain -- freedom," Yeltsin
said.
</P>
<P>
"We have saved for Russia a worthy place in the world
community and we have not allowed Russia to slide down to a
dictatorship. We have prevented chaos and opened the door to a
normal life," he said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin noted that for the first time in this century, power
is being legitimately handed over from one head of state to
another in Russia.
</P>
<P>
"We can be proud that this is being done peacefully, without
revolutions and putsches, in a respectful and free way," he said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin handed over to Putin the Order for Service to
Fatherland, first degree, the symbol of presidential authority.
</P>
<P>
"I'm passing over to Putin the symbol of presidential
authority and, most important, responsibility for the future of
the nation and all Russian citizens," Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
He wished Putin success and asked him to "take care of Russia
and protect it." 
</P>
