<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi has
warned some politicians against calls that local people invade
property owned by foreign companies or people of foreign origin,
saying that it was a recipe to chaos.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan Member of Parliament Stephen Ndicho mobilized landless
Kenyans to invade farms owned by white farmers last month.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Nation newspaper quoted Moi as saying that such
behavior was " cheap politics" because the politician did this out
of party interests.
</P>
<P>
"Ndicho is telling people to invade farms owned by white farms.
The MP's call is meant to incite Africans to attack one another,"
Moi told a gathering on Saturday in central Kenyan town of
Naivasha, where many white farmers have invested in horticulture.
</P>
<P>
The president said reckless talk by some politicians was
undermining the government efforts to woo tourists and other
investors. 
</P>
