<HEADLINE> Love Bug Hit Chinese Computers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing-based Ruixing Computer Company received reports of
computer paralysation from domestic PC users just in hours of the
spread of the virus infection. Computer engineers of the company
cleaned out the virus in 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Anti-virus expert Liu Xu said there was no large-scale outbreak
of computer shutdown in China as a result of a May 1 International
Labor Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
Liu advised PC users of necessary precautions to protect
themselves against potential virus attacks when holiday-goers
return to work.
</P>
<P>
The virus has hit more than 1 million computers around the
world as from May 4.  
</P>
</TEXT>
