<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Water Project Benefits 3.5 Million Ethnic People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- About 3.5 million ethnic minority
people in central China's Hunan Province have benefited from a
drinking water supply project, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Funded by 5.41 million US dollars from the World Bank and the
provincial government, the project has solved the problem of
insufficient drinking water for ethnic groups and livestock in
remote mountainous areas, where natural conditions are harsh and
infrastructure backward.
</P>
<P>
The population of the ethnic groups living in these areas is 5.
5 million. They have suffered from a severe shortage of drinking
water, which has affected not only local economic development but
also the people's health.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the water project, 3.5 million people and three
million animals in the areas now have enough water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
