<HEADLINE> Congress "Steel 2000" Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The largest international steel
conference in China, "Steel 2000," opens today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The event consists of one symposium on steel development
strategy, which covers topics ranging from policies, trade,
financing, environmental protection to e-business, and six
symposiums focusing on technologies.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 delegates from enterprises, governments, research
and financial institutions in more than 20 countries including
China, Germany, Japan, the United States and Russia are attending
the event.
</P>
<P>
The five-day event is jointly sponsored by China's State
Administration of Metallurgical Industry, China Iron and Steel
Association, Metallurgical Council of China and China Council for
the Promotion of International Trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
