<HEADLINE> "LoveLetter" Virus Enters Chinese Computer Networks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- The software virus named "I LOVE YOU
" which crippled computer networks around the world Thursday hit
more than 100 computers in China, "China Youth Daily" reports
today.
</P>
<P>
Beijing-based Ruixing Computer Company received reports of
computer paralisation from domestic PC users just in hours of the
spread of the virus infection. Computer engineers of the company
cleaned out the virus in 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Anti-virus expert Liu Xu said there was no large-scale outbreak
of computer shutdown in China as a result of a week-long May 1
International Labor Day holiday vacation.
</P>
<P>
Liu advised PC users of necessary precautions to protect
themselves against potential virus attacks when holiday-goers
return to work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
