<HEADLINE> Defense University Becomes Cradle of Military Talents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 7 (Xinhua) -- China's National Defense Science and
Technology University recently granted academic degrees to 300 Ph.
D. and Master students, becoming the leading military science
training center in China.
</P>
<P>
Since the university resumed enrollment of post-graduates in
1978, 3,735 master-degree students and 333 Ph.D. students have
graduated from the school, "China Youth Daily" reports today.
</P>
<P>
The university attaches great importance to students' ability
of research and innovation. Students have taken part in a large
portion of the 3,400 research items carried out by the university.
</P>
<P>
Among researchers of the Milky Way ultra-large computer system,
60 percent were post-graduates. Some have won the Science Progress
Prize while they studied at the university.  
</P>
</TEXT>
