<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0040 GMT, May 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Italy has over nine million Internet users who are
mostly male and access the web from homes in the north of Italy,
the Italian thinktank Censis found in a survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey found 21.3 percent of its sample used the net,
showing a sharp rise on recent studies but still lagging far
behind the United States where 55 percent of the population have
access to the web. (Italy-Internet Users)
</P>
