<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indiana Beats 76ers at Semifinal Series Operner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Indiana Pacers roared to a 108-
91 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers in the opener of their NBA
Eastern Conference semifinal series on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Reggie Miller and Jalen Rose scored 40 points apiece and both
hit the floor gunning as the Pacers raced to a 34-15 first-quarter
lead in their home court.
</P>
<P>
Miller scored 16 of his 40 points in the first quarter. He
made 11-of-18 shots, including seven 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
Rose contributed 11 of his career-high 40 in the opening
period. He was 16-of-23 from the field, including three 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
Together, Miller and Rose became the first pair of Pacers and
only the fourth playoff duo to score 40 points in the same game.
The last to do it were Houston's Hakeem Olajuwon and Clyde Drexler
against Utah on May 5, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Coming off four days of rest following a first-round series
win over Charlotte, the 76ers trailed 9-0 after 3 1/2 minutes and
never led.
</P>
<P>
When Philadelphia surged within six points midway through the
third quarter, Miller and Rose rose up again. The duo combined for
26 straight Indiana points over a 15-minute span beginning in the
second period.
</P>
<P>
The Pacers led 78-69 entering the fourth quarter and never let
the Sixers get closer than eight points.
</P>
<P>
Iverson, who led the Sixers with 28 points, stalked referee
Ken Mauer, yelling in his face while accidentally bumping into him.
Iverson was ejected with 2:53 left.
</P>
<P>
Game 2 of the best-of-seven series will be played in
Indianapolis on Monday, but it is unclear whether Iverson will be
available or under a suspension.  
</P>
</TEXT>
