<HEADLINE> hke050701-- Report: 2 Headless Bodies of Basilan Hostages Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 7 (Xinhua) -- Two headless bodies from the group of
Basilan hostages have been found near a camp of Abu Sayyaf rebels
in Basilan, the Southern Philippines, the local ABS-CBN television
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It said the two bodies were found Saturday some 20 meters away
from Camp Abdurazzak in Sumisip, Basilan.
</P>
<P>
Last Wednesday, Philippine government troops rescued 15
hostages in an encounter with the Abu Sayyaf rebels, but they
found that four hostages, including a priest had been killed by
the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The Abu Sayyaf group took away more than 50 people from two
schools in Basilan as human shield on March 20. Later, it held 29
as hostages and freed the rest.
</P>
<P>
The remaining hostages are believed still in the hands of the
rebel group. 
</P>
