<HEADLINE> Regional Seminar on Cooperation Ends in Havana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The Regional Seminar on Cooperation
for Development in Latin America and the Caribbean ended in Havana
Saturday after approving a report to be presented to a special
forum in June in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from 16 Latin American and Caribbean countries and
international institutions and non-government organizations
discussed ways to make the cooperation more effective.
</P>
<P>
They were briefed on the results of dozens of local economic
projects of international cooperation in such sectors as
environment, education, health, and social services.
</P>
<P>
They also evaluated decentralized cooperation, culture for
social and human development, and also the best use of human,
natural, and financial resources, among others.
</P>
<P>
The three-day seminar was organized by the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and the Cuban Ministry for Foreign
Investment and Economic Cooperation. 
</P>
