PANAMA CITY -- The surprise attack of the so-called "Love bug"
(ILOVEYOU) failed before the anti-virus activity of the Panama
Canal Authority (ACP), although it affected the administrative
side, the local press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ruben Reina, manager of the Customers Division and manager of
ACP Information Department, said that the canal is operating
normally, in spite of the fact that the users of the ACP
information system began to receive an immense quantity of
messages with the title "I LOVE YOU."  (Panama Canal-Virus)
