<HEADLINE> Arsenal Moves Close to Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 6 (Xinhua) -- Arsenal took a giant leap to next
season's European Champions League when the team, with double from
Thierry Henry, defeated Chelsea 2-1 at an Englsh premier league
match on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Champions Manchester United cruised to a 3-1 home win over
Tottenham Hotspur to take their points tally to 88 with one game
remaining.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal, with two games left have 72. Leeds United, who play
Everton on Monday, have 67 with Liverpool fourth on 66 ahead of
their home game against Southampton on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea are fifth on 63 and cannot make the top three for a
Champions League place or even fourth for a berth in the UEFA Cup
and now must win the FA Cup to be playing in Europe next season.
</P>
<P>
At the bottom, Wimbledon gave themselves a lifeline when John
Hartson headed an injury time equaliser to clinch a 2-2 home draw
with Aston Villa. The point takes Wimbledon above Bradford City,
who lost 3-0 at Leicester City, on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Sheffield Wednesday lost 4-1 at Coventry City and are almost
certainly down.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games Kevin Phillips scored his 30th league
goal of the season to give Sunderland a 1-0 home win over West Ham
United, Middlesbrough drew 1-1 at home with relegated Watford
while Derby County ensured their survival with a goalless home
draw against Newcastle United. 
</P>
</TEXT>
