<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bayern Munich Wins DFB Cup for the Tenth Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, May 6 (Xinhua) -- The finals of the Cup of the German
Football Association DFB was played on Saturday evening with
Bayern Munich winning the title for the tenth time.
</P>
<P>
Some 76,000 fans packed Berlin's Olympic Stadium. Bayern
Munich, last season's losing finalists, took revenge over Werder
Bremen with a 3-0 win.
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless first half, Bayern Munich mounted their
offensive in the second half. Brazilian Giovane Elber opened the
scoring gate for Bayern Munich with a left-foot in the 57th minute.
</P>
<P>
Another Brazilian Paulo Sergio made it 2-0 for Bayern while
German international Mehmet Scholl sealed the perfect victory with
a goal in injury time.
</P>
<P>
This season Bayern Munich again have the chance to win the
titles of the German Bundesliga and the European Champions League.
They are now three points behind Bundesliga leaders BAyer
Leverkusen and are still in contention in the European Champions
League.
</P>
<P>
Last season Bayern Munich's hopes of winning the "treble" were
dashed as they were defeated by Manchester United in the Champions
League final and were defeated by Werder Bremen in the German DFB
Cup final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
