<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said here Sunday
that the withdrawal from south Lebanon will not affect Israel's
capability to retaliate any cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Barak told the cabinet that the government is ready to provide
more economic assistance to the residents of the confrontation line
along the northern border.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet met Sunday to discuss recent developments in the
north, particularly the tense situation following Hezbollah's
rocket attacks last weekend against northern Israel. (BC-Israel-
Lebanon-Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian chief negotiator in the final- status talks
Yasser Abed Rabbo on Sunday totally rejected the Israeli-drawn
redeployment maps presented in the Eilat talks.
</P>
<P>
Rabbo made the statement after discussing with U.S. Mideast
peace envoy Dennis Ross in the West Bank the maps and the Israeli-
made obstacles against the peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Israel proposes to hand over to the Palestinians 66 percent of
the West Bank, according to the maps. (BC-Palestine-Redeployment-
Maps)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Sunday rejected allegations by foreign media
that Iranians were involved in the Lockerbie bombing in 1988.
</P>
<P>
These futile and baseless allegations are totally unacceptable,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi was quoted by the
Islamic News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman was amazed over the claims made in some interviews
and materials printed by some foreign media, saying the allegations
were made to influence the court hearing, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The bombing of Pan American Flight 103 over Lockerbie, Scotland
in December 1988 killed 259 people in the air and 11 people on the
ground.(BC-Iran-Lockerbie-Denial)
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The summit between Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat started in the West Bank City of
Ramallah Sunday evening to clear the obstacles in the bilateral
peace talks, Radio Israel reported.
</P>
<P>
The summit was also attended by Secretary of the Palestine
Liberation Organization Mahmoud Abbas, Speaker of Palestinian
Legislative Council Ahmed Qureia, Barak's political and security
adviser Danny Yatom and his Foreign Minister David Levy.
(Palestine-Israel-Summit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
