<HEADLINE> Britain Deploys Troops over Sierra Leone Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 7 (Xinhua) -- A battalion of paratroopers, a Royal
Navy frigate and a helicopter carrier are being dispatched to
Sierra Leone to help Britons trapped by violence in the West
African country.
</P>
<P>
Defense Secretary Geoff Hoon said he was deploying the first
Battalion of the Parachute Regiment, about 700-800 men including
support staff as well as the helicopter carrier HMS Ocean, the
frigate HMS Chatham and three support ships.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Defense stressed the deployments were"
precautionary measures to ensure that we are best placed to
respond quickly to safeguard the security of British nationals, if
that becomes necessary".
</P>
<P>
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook has advised Britons to consider
leaving Sierra Leone unless they have essential business there.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office also announced that non-essential support
staff at the High Commission in the capital Freetown, and their
dependents, are being withdrawn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
